# Gitignore-syntax patterns for project-owned paths.
#
# Prefix conventions:
#   pattern      → project-owned (P3 never proposes relocation).
#   ?pattern     → safety-net: should NOT be committed. A committed match is
#                  a hygiene warning; an unmatched rule is informational only.
#   !pattern     → negation: force back into branch-introduction derivation.
#
# Later entries override earlier ones, per gitignore semantics.
# See cascade/docs/ownership.md.

# Lockfiles — legitimately committed at the repo root only. Patterns are
# anchored with a leading slash so that nested lockfiles (e.g.
# cascade/package-lock.json, container/agent-runner/package-lock.json) fall
# through to history-based ownership derivation and get attributed to the
# module/skill that owns them.
/package-lock.json
/yarn.lock
/pnpm-lock.yaml

# Safety-net: shouldn't be committed
?node_modules/
?vendor/
?dist/
?build/
?*.generated.ts
?*.generated.js
?container/*.tgz
